--highlight\">Codex</span> <span class=\"algolia-docsearch-suggestion--highlight\">app</span>, you can also start a chat without choosing a project. Chats\n<span class=\"algolia-docsearch-suggestion--highlight\">aren’t</span> tied to a saved <span class=\"algolia-docsearch-suggestion--highlight\">repository</span> or project folder. Use them for research,\nplanning, connected-tool workflows, or other work where <span class=\"algolia-docsearch-suggestion--highlight\">Codex</span> shouldn’t start\nfrom a codebase. Chats use a <span class=\"algolia-docsearch-suggestion--highlight\">Codex</span>-managed threads directory under your <span class=\"algolia-docsearch-suggestion--highlight\">Codex</span>\nhome as their working location. By default, that location is ~/.<span class=\"algolia-docsearch-suggestion--highlight\">codex</span>/threads.\nTo change the base location for this state, set <span class=\"algolia-docsearch-suggestion--highlight\">CODEX</span>_HOME; see\nConfig and state locations.",
