### Extend Vercel Sandbox Session Timeout (TypeScript)

Source: https://vercel.com/docs/rest-api/sandboxes/extend-session-timeout

This snippet demonstrates how to send a POST request to the Vercel API to extend a sandbox session's timeout. It requires an authorization bearer token and specifies the duration in milliseconds.

```TypeScript
const response = await fetch('https://api.vercel.com/v2/sandboxes/sessions/sessionId/extend-timeout?teamId=string&slug=string', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Authorization': 'Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN',
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    "duration": "300000"
  }),
});

const data = await response.json();
console.log(data);
```

